All Dogs Go to Heaven is a classic Don Bluth movie. I grew up watching it. I feel I should caution anyone who hasn't seen it buying it for young children. Bluth films are not Disney; there is death, alcohol, and gambling. There's nothing graphic or inappropriate, but those elements are present.
As for the actual product, there are two discs included, one for each movie. It's just your basic double feature. There aren't any special features, which makes sense since neither of the films were originally intended for DVD. The product isn't really anything special, but the movies work and it was exactly what I expected.
